summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions on Western Sahara, reaffirms its support for the Secretary-General's efforts and commitment to a just, lasting, and mutually acceptable political solution for self-determination. It calls on parties to cooperate, notes Moroccan and Polisario Front proposals, and considers the Secretary-General's report. The Council: 

1. Reaffirms respect for military agreements with MINURSO; 
2. Calls for negotiations without preconditions in good faith; 
3. Requests the Secretary-General to set up negotiations under his auspices; 
4. Requests a report by 30 June 2007 on negotiation progress; 
5. Requests a report on the situation before the end of the mandate period; 
6. Calls for voluntary contributions for Confidence Building Measures; 
7. Requests zero-tolerance policy enforcement on sexual exploitation and abuse; 
8. Extends MINURSO's mandate until 31 October 2007; 
9. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
